race.comment: OUR NEMESIS (4) got into a good race fresh before winning over this track and trip last time out, winning by 0.3L. He rises in weight off that effort, but should be better again third-up and with the aid of an inside barrier. Faithfull remains in the saddle and he looks the one to beat. SACRED OATH (5) finished 0.3L off the winner last start over this course and distance when right in the market. He was on the quick turnaround there however and now hits this third-up, a spot where he's won previously. Likely to get back in the run but can finish over the top of them. PRAY AGAIN (6) stormed home fresh at Northam in a CL3 and looks well placed here up in trip. He has raced well second-up in the past and Yuill replaces the apprentice hoop. Can build on the fresh effort. MAGIC MIKEY (8) just missed first-up and can be in the finish again today. HANG GLIDER (2) should appreciate the rise in trip and is worth including off a good effort last start.
